# Sub-collections

Sub-collections are located in the `src/collections` directory.

Database collection services are located in the `src/services/database` directory.

## Create a new sub-collection

Always ask for the name of the sub-collection and parent collection to confirm it is correct, don't start writing anything until you have both names.

- If the sub-collection name already have the parent collection name in it, remove it, for example:
  - Parent collection: `users`
  - Sub-collection: `user-messages`
  - Sub-collection name would be: `messages`
- File name: `{parent in singular form}-{sub-collection in singular form}.collection.ts`, for example:
  - Parent collection: `users`
  - Sub-collection: `messages`
  - File name would be: `user-message.collection.ts` (use singular form)
- Interface name: `{Parent in singular form}{Sub-collection in singular form}`, for example:
  - Parent collection: `users`
  - Sub-collection: `messages`
  - Interface name would be: `UserMessage` (use singular form)
- Use the following template and don't add any other fields:

```typescript
export interface UserMessage {
  additionalData: Record<string, unknown>;
  createdAt: Date;
  id: string;
  updatedAt: Date;
}
```

- After creating the sub-collection, create the file for the service: `{parent in singular form}-{sub-collection in plural form}.service.ts`, for example:
  - Parent collection: `users`
  - Sub-collection: `messages`
  - File name would be: `user-messages.service.ts` (use singular and plural form)
- Use the following template:

```typescript
import { Transaction, WriteBatch } from 'firebase-admin/firestore';
import { Result } from 'neverthrow';
import { UserMessage } from '../../collections/user-message.collection';
import { Logger } from '../../utils/logging.utils';
import { GenericError } from '../../utils/result.utils';
import { CollectionService } from '../collection.service';
import { DatabaseService } from '../database.service';

type UserMessageCreateData = Omit<UserMessage, 'createdAt' | 'id' | 'updatedAt'>;

type UserMessageUpdateData = UserMessageUpdateAdditionalData;

type UserMessageUpdateAdditionalData = Pick<UserMessage, 'additionalData'>;

export class UserMessagesService extends CollectionService<UserMessage> {
  private static instance: UserMessagesService;
  static getInstance(): UserMessagesService {
    if (!UserMessagesService.instance) {
      // Use the parent collection name and the sub-collection name to create the path, remove this comment after creating the service
      UserMessagesService.instance = new UserMessagesService('users/userMessages');
    }
    return UserMessagesService.instance;
  }

  override createDocument(db: DatabaseService, data: UserMessageCreateData, logger: Logger, config?: {
    id?: string;
    parentId?: string;
  }): Promise<Result<string, GenericError>>;
  override createDocument(db: DatabaseService, data: UserMessageCreateData, logger: Logger, config?: {
    batch?: WriteBatch;
    id?: string;
    parentId?: string;
    transaction?: Transaction;
  }): Result<string, GenericError>;
  override createDocument(db: DatabaseService, data: UserMessageCreateData, logger: Logger, config?: {
    batch?: WriteBatch;
    id?: string;
    parentId?: string;
    transaction?: Transaction;
  }): Promise<Result<string, GenericError>> | Result<string, GenericError> {
    return super.createDocument(db, data, logger, config);
  }

  override updateDocument(db: DatabaseService, documentId: string, updateData: UserMessageUpdateData, logger: Logger, config?: {
    ignoreTimestamp?: boolean;
    parentId?: string;
  }): Promise<Result<void, GenericError>>;
  override updateDocument(db: DatabaseService, documentId: string, updateData: UserMessageUpdateData, logger: Logger, config?: {
    batch?: WriteBatch;
    ignoreTimestamp?: boolean;
    parentId?: string;
    transaction?: Transaction;
  }): Result<void, GenericError>;
  override updateDocument(db: DatabaseService, documentId: string, updateData: UserMessageUpdateData, logger: Logger, config?: {
    batch?: WriteBatch;
    ignoreTimestamp?: boolean;
    parentId?: string;
    transaction?: Transaction;
  }): Promise<Result<void, GenericError>> | Result<void, GenericError> {
    return super.updateDocument(db, documentId, updateData, logger, config);
  }
}
```
